column18: 07/02/2007: Three policemen were attacked by militants with a home-made petrol bomb in Western Sahara. The officers were burned in the incident in Western Sahara which has been occupied by Morocco since 1975.  No claim of responsibility was reported.
column125: The reason why the psychological damage is listed as moderate is because this event may lead to strain or a break down in negotiations that the Moroccan government is going through with the Polisario Front.
